What it is: A collection of questions about ages 0-12.

What it contains:

Categories: Family environment, curiosity, confidence, social development, challenge/failure

Each question has: The question itself, its purpose, its tone

Follow-up strategies: What to say based on user response

Example
"What was the one question you kept asking as a child?" → Reveals curiosity pattern
"Who in your family made you feel like you could be completely yourself?" → Reveals attachment style
Why you need it: You can't ask good questions on the fly. This is your curated question library.
